[@Cucurbit downy mildew#Disease*], caused by the oomycete [$Pseudoperonospora cubensis#Virus*], is a devastating, worldwide-distributed disease of [$cucurbit crops#Plant*] in the open field and under cover.
This review provides recent data on the taxonomy, biology, ecology, host range, geographic distribution and epidemiology of [$P.cubensis#Virus*].
