Genetics and variability of host resistance and cellular and molecular aspects of such resistance are considered.
A focus is given to methods of [$crop#Plant*] protection, including prevention and agrotechnical aspects, breeding for resistance-classical and transgenic approaches, chemical control and fungicide resistance.
Novel technologies in biological and integrated control are also discussed.
This review also summarizes the most important topics for future research and international collaboration.
